free download </a>
<h2> Notepad - Turn Word Wrap on or off</h2>
The Word Wrap and Font options are only available via the Format menu. Word Wrap has never been enabled by default in Notepad for whatever reason that has never been discovered.

Everything you input will appear on a single long line until you hit Enter, at which point a new line will appear above the previous one. You can press Enter when your typing is about to approach the right edge of the Notepad window. However, doing so will cause the lines to be of a random length and vary depending on your window size.
<h3>Notepad - Save Documents as HTML files</h3>
You may also generate HTML files by using the Notepad program. Ensure that the Word Wrap option is selected, and then input your HTML code the same way you would type ordinary text.

When it's time to save your work, go to the File menu, choose Save As, and select All Files from the list of options. Then, choose either the.htm or.html extension when you save your work.
<h2>Conclusion</h2>
Notepad is a desktop application that has been available for quite some time and continues to help create simple text and HTML. There are times when that is all that is required.

Picture Notes is an excellent option if you need more features than the fundamental ones.

