ader_size":"h1","align":"center"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"heading"},{"id":"a0ad0ce","elType":"widget","settings":{"space":{"unit":"px","size":20,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"widgetType":"spacer"},{"id":"e1e9d67","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p><span style=\"color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight );\"><img src=\"https:\/\/picturenotes.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/notepad.png\" alt=\"Notepad App logo\" width=\"256\" height=\"256\" \/><\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight );\">Windows comes pre-installed with a straightforward text editor called Notepad. It works well for producing very brief text documents you intend to keep in their original plain text format.\u00a0<\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight );\">That is one of many things that can be done with it. You may be shocked by how simple Notepad is, mainly if you have not used it often. Notepad only provides a limited number of customization possibilities.\u00a0<\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight );\">Therefore, more customization is optional. You should see options for File, Edit, Format, View, and help at the top of the window where you work. Let's look at Notepad's features and see what it can do for you.\u00a0<\/span><\/p><p>Remember that Notepad is merely a text editor, even though everything should seem comfortable and familiar to you. It will not function if you attempt to copy and paste any visuals into it.<\/p><h2><strong>Uses of Notepad App<\/strong><\/h2><p>Create, Read, and Save Text Files<\/p><p>Under the \"File\" menu, you may select either \"New\" or \"New Windows,\" as well as \"Open,\" \"Save,\" \"Save As,\" \"Page Setup,\" and \"Print.\" As can be seen, several of these commands also include shortcuts that may be entered using the keyboard.<\/p><p>Because they are consistent across most Windows applications, you are already familiar with some of them.<\/p><h3><span style=\"font-weight: bolder; color: var( --e-global-color-primary ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-primary-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: 2rem;\">Notepad<\/span><span style=\"font-weight: bolder; color: var( --e-global-color-primary ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-primary-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: 2rem;\">\u00a0-\u00a0<\/span>Text Editing<\/h3><p>The Edit menu provides a selection of options, but every item on this menu should be recognizable to everyone who has ever worked with Windows. Each of the Edit menu options has a corresponding shortcut on the keyboard.<\/p><p>Unless the text is selected in the Notepad window, most instructions are hidden behind a gray background. When revising the document, you can utilize the Undo\/Redo function at the top of the Edit menu.<\/p><h3><span style=\"font-weight: bolder; color: var( --e-global-color-primary ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-primary-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: 2rem;\">Notepad<\/span><span style=\"font-weight: bolder; color: var( --e-global-color-primary ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-primary-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: 2rem;\">\u00a0-\u00a0<\/span>Text Searches and Replacements<\/h3><p>Find, Find Next, and Replace are the commands utilized to search and replace text inside the document, while Go-To is the power used to traverse through the paper. Suppose you wish to search for a piece of text or replace it with something else.<\/p><p>In that case, you may do either by selecting the Find option (accessible through the keyboard shortcut Ctrl + F) or the Replace option (accessible via the keyboard shortcut Ctrl + H).<\/p><p>That will cause Notepad to open a new window where the \"Find what\" area allows you to enter the text you are looking for. If you wish to replace text, the Replace box will also provide a field to enter what you want to replace it with.<\/p>","column_gap":{"unit":"px","size":0,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"},{"id":"0ac1969","elType":"widget","settings":{"layout":"right","bg_image":{"url":"https:\/\/picturenotes.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/banner.png","id":238,"alt":"","source":"library"},"bg_image_size":"full","bg_image_custom_dimension":{"width":"3000","height":"450"},"title":"Download the app now","description":"Picture Notes is the visual notepad that help you to organise your images, video, recording and files to easily locate them later \u2013 and the best part, you can use emojis \ud83d\ude0e\ud83d\udc4a\n","button":"free download ","link":{"url":"https:\/\/play.google.com\/store\/apps\/details?id=com.organize.data","is_external":"","nofollow":"","custom_attributes":""},"min-height":{"unit":"px","size":175,"sizes":[]},"image_min_width":{"unit":"px","size":500,"sizes":[]},"image_min_height":{"unit":"px","size":70,"sizes":[]},"image_min_height_tablet":{"unit":"vh","size":"","sizes":[]},"image_min_height_mobile":{"unit":"vh","size":"","sizes":[]},"title_spacing":{"unit":"px","size":13,"sizes":[]},"description_spacing":{"unit":"px","size":21,"sizes":[]},"button_size":"md","button_text_color":"#000000","button_border_width":{"unit":"px","size":1,"sizes":[]},"button_border_radius":{"unit":"px","size":86,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"widgetType":"call-to-action"},{"id":"3a169c0","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p><\/p>\n<h2>&nbsp;Notepad<span style=\"color: var( --e-global-color-primary ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-primary-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-weight: bolder; font-size: 2rem;\">&nbsp;-&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"color: var( --e-global-color-primary ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-primary-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-primary-font-weight );\">Turn Word Wrap on or off<\/span><\/h2>\n<p>The Word Wrap and Font options are only available via the Format menu. Word Wrap has never been enabled by default in Notepad for whatever reason that has never been discovered.<\/p>\n<p>Everything you input will appear on a single long line until you hit Enter, at which point a new line will appear above the previous one. You can press Enter when your typing is about to approach the right edge of the Notepad window.&nbsp;<span style=\"color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight );\">However, doing so will cause the lines to be of a random length and vary depending on your window size.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bolder; color: var( --e-global-color-primary ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-primary-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: 2rem;\">Notepad -<\/span><span style=\"font-weight: bolder; color: var( --e-global-color-primary ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-primary-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: 2rem;\">&nbsp;<\/span>Save Documents as HTML files<\/h3>\n<p>You may also generate HTML files by using the Notepad program. Ensure that the Word Wrap option is selected, and then input your HTML code the same way you would type ordinary text.<\/p>\n<p>When it's time to save your work, go to the File menu, choose Save As, and select All Files from the list of options. Then, choose either the.htm or.html extension when you save your work.<\/p>\n<h2>Conclusion<\/h2>\n<p>Notepad is a desktop application that has been available for quite some time and continues to help create simple text and HTML. There are times when that is all that is required.<\/p>\n<p>Picture Notes is an excellent option if you need more features than the fundamental ones.<\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight );\">Try&nbsp;<\/span><a style=\"font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight ); background-color: #ffffff;\" href=\"https:\/\/play.google.com\/store\/apps\/details?id=com.organize.data\">Picture Note for free<\/a><\/p>","column_gap":{"unit":"px","size":0,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":false}],"isInner":false},{"id":"b612975","elType":"section","settings":{"background_background":"classic","background_color":"#FDFDFD","background_color_stop":{"unit":"%","size":8,"sizes":[]},"background_color_b":"#FFFFFF"},"elements":[{"id":"ce6fa07","elType":"column","settings":{"_column_size":100,"_inline_size":null},"elements":[{"id":"f8f8561","elType":"widget","settings":{"style":"dotted","text":"Divider"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"divider"},{"id":"050938a","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<h2 style=\"font-family: var( --e-global-typography-primary-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-primary-font-weight );\"><a href=\"https:\/\/play.google.com\/store\/apps\/details?id=com.organize.data\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-382\" style=\"font-size: 16px;\" src=\"https:\/\/picturenotes.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/cropped-Artboard-9-300x300.png\" alt=\"Note taking apps\" width=\"133\" height=\"133\" \/><\/a><\/h2><h2><a href=\"https:\/\/play.google.com\/store\/apps\/details?id=com.organize.data\">Picture Notes<\/a><\/h2><p>Picture Notes is a new rapidly growing personal note taking app focused around organising your gallery. It is hosted in the cloud and is ideal for the creation of notes containing imagery as well as taking memos.\u00a0<\/p><p>You can rapidly format your notes in\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/picturenotes.co.uk\/\">Picture Notes\u2019<\/a>\u00a0editor, which features a streamlined and uncluttered design, by adding headings, detailed descriptions, reminders, numbered lists, and other elements.\u00a0<\/p><p>You can enhance the visual quality of your notes by inserting photographs, PDF\u2019s, videos, music, and many different file types.<\/p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":false}],"isInner":false}]]]></wp:meta_value>
